title.narrative: Output 5.2: More teachers have core knowledge and competencies to use proven teaching methodologies to deliver appropriatequality education.

description.narrative: UNICEF provided technical assistance to develop an investment case to increase financing and access to quality Early Childhood Care, Development, and education services. UNICEF supported the capacity development of 27,806 teachers on teaching and learning pedagogy with mentoring and coaching, contributing to increased teacher attendance from 71% in 2020 to 80% in 2021 in UNICEF focus states. At least 1,426,762 children received support with catch-up learning programmes through home, community-based, and digital learning solutions to mitigate learning loss due to COVID-19. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:29/12/2021
